Review the commands folder. I want to add a new github-fix-issue command to the available commands. It should follow the same format as the rest of the commands. It should use gh issue view to get the issue details, understand the problem described in the issue, search the codebase for relevant files, determine the root cause of the issue. Then it should generate a plan to resolve the issue and propose the necessary changes to fix the issue to the user with a proposed todo list. Once the plan is approved, execute the necessary changes. Once completed,  ensure code passes linting and type checking.
